# EktaMandi Voice Assistant - AI Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your API keys

# ── Option 1: Groq (FREE tier - recommended) ──
# Sign up at https://console.groq.com and get a free API key
# Free tier: 30 requests/min, supports Llama 3
VITE_GROQ_API_KEY=
VITE_GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile

# ── Option 2: Amazon Bedrock (via proxy) ──
# Requires a backend proxy that forwards requests to AWS Bedrock
# Set up an API Gateway + Lambda that calls Bedrock
# VITE_BEDROCK_PROXY_URL=https://your-api-gateway.amazonaws.com/prod/chat
# VITE_BEDROCK_MODEL=anthropic.claude-3-haiku-20240307-v1:0

# ── No keys? No problem! ──
# The voice assistant works fully without AI using rule-based responses.
# AI just adds natural conversation ability on top.
